WEBVTT

00:00.930 --> 00:02.477
- YOU GOT A TEXT
FROM ED BROOKS.

00:02.510 --> 00:04.307
YOU GUYS HAVE BEEN TEXTING
EACH OTHER A LOT LATELY.

00:04.340 --> 00:07.446
- I NEED YOU TO STOP CALLING ME.
IT'S NOT FAIR TO JOEL.

00:07.490 --> 00:10.106
- I LIKE HIM.
I LIKE MAX.

00:10.140 --> 00:11.550
I'M NOT SAYING
HE DOESN'T HAVE HIS MOMENTS,

00:11.590 --> 00:13.797
BUT I'M SHOWING HIM THE ROPES
AND IT'S GOOD FOR HIM,

00:13.840 --> 00:15.455
AND IT'S GOOD FOR ME.

00:15.490 --> 00:16.525
- ARE YOU HAVING A GREAT TIME?
- IT'S JUST BEEN AMAZING.

00:16.560 --> 00:20.348
- I MISS YOU.
- GOT TO GO.

00:20.390 --> 00:21.596
- WE CAN'T SLEEP TOGETHER
AGAIN, OKAY?

00:21.640 --> 00:23.426
- OKAY.

00:23.470 --> 00:26.496
- MAYBE WE SHOULD BE
JUST FRIENDS.

00:26.540 --> 00:27.359
- HI.

00:29.540 --> 00:32.600
DURING THE WEEK
WE HAVE CAST PARTIES

00:32.650 --> 00:34.197
AND ON THE WEEKEND, WE--
- YOU HAVE THEM DURING THE WEEK?

00:34.240 --> 00:35.195
- YES, DURING THE WEEK.
- JEEZ.

00:35.240 --> 00:36.161
[smacks cards]
both: OH.

00:36.200 --> 00:37.781
OH, NO!
- OH, YEAH. I WON.

00:37.830 --> 00:39.274
- WHAT? NO, BECAUSE--
- MY HAND IS UNDER YOUR HAND.

00:39.310 --> 00:40.618
- I DON'T THINK THAT WAS WHAT--
- BECAUSE WHAT?

00:40.660 --> 00:43.106
[knocking at the door]
- OH. COME IN.

00:43.140 --> 00:45.313
- OH, MY GOD,
I GOT SO LOST ON THE BART.

00:45.350 --> 00:46.510
IT WAS, LIKE,
SUCH A DISASTER.

00:46.560 --> 00:49.211
- HEY.

00:49.250 --> 00:51.696
- OH. HI.

00:51.740 --> 00:53.310
I THOUGHT YOU'D BE ALONE.
- YEAH, THIS IS MY FRIEND.

00:53.360 --> 00:54.520
- HI.
- THIS IS AMY.

00:54.570 --> 00:56.492
SHE--SHE'S IN FROM OUT OF TOWN.
SHE GOES TO TUFI'S, BUT--

00:56.530 --> 00:58.669
- I'M NATALIE.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

00:58.710 --> 01:01.395
- NICE TO MEET YOU.

01:01.440 --> 01:04.398
_ UM--
- COOL, COOL.

01:04.440 --> 01:08.365
- WE'RE JUST PLAYING CARDS,
IF YOU--YOU WANT TO PLAY?

01:08.410 --> 01:09.570
- NO, I'LL JUST--
I'LL CATCH YOU LATER.

01:09.620 --> 01:11.611
IT WAS NICE, UH,
MEETING YOU.

01:11.650 --> 01:13.163
- BYE.
- YEAH, BYE.

01:13.210 --> 01:14.199
- BYE.

01:17.760 --> 01:19.751
- SHE'S CUTE.

01:19.800 --> 01:22.109
_ UH--
- IS THAT YOUR GIRLFRIEND?

01:22.150 --> 01:23.651
- NO. SHE, UM--

01:23.700 --> 01:25.736
NO, SHE JUST LIVES
DOWN THE HALL, SO--

01:25.770 --> 01:27.829
- THAT'S CONVENIENT.
[chuckles]

01:27.880 --> 01:32.396
- SHE DOES THAT THING, THE,
LIKE, DRUNKENLY DROPPING IN.

01:32.430 --> 01:34.364
I GUESS SHE'S KIND OF
KNOWN FOR THAT.

01:34.400 --> 01:35.537
- IT'S OKAY, I'M KIDDING.

01:35.570 --> 01:36.810
I'M JOKING.
- YEAH, I KNOW. I WAS JUST--

01:36.850 --> 01:40.536
I WAS JUST SAYING.
[chuckles]

01:40.580 --> 01:42.366
WANT TO KEEP PLAYING?
- YEAH.

01:42.410 --> 01:43.399
- ALL RIGHT.
[laughs]

01:43.440 --> 01:45.613
[doorbell clings]

01:45.650 --> 01:48.210
- WHO IS IT?
- MRS. CRABBLES.

01:48.240 --> 01:49.343
- WHO?
- CARL.

01:49.380 --> 01:51.894
- WHO?
- HA HA. DID YOU ORDER CHINESE?

01:51.930 --> 01:54.239
- YOU CAN SMELL THAT
ALL THE WAY OUT IN THE HALLWAY?

01:54.280 --> 01:55.929
- I HAVE
A VERY SENSITIVE NOSE.

01:55.970 --> 01:57.380
HEY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING
FRIDAY NIGHT?

01:57.420 --> 01:58.830
- WHY?

01:58.870 --> 02:00.804
- UH, I HAVE TO GO
TO THIS CHARITY THING,

02:00.840 --> 02:02.808
AND THOUGHT YOU MIGHT
WANT TO GO WITH ME.

02:02.840 --> 02:07.607
- THANK YOU, CARL, BUT I HAVE
TOLD YOU THAT I WILL NOT BE--

02:07.640 --> 02:10.359
- SLEEP WITH ME.
YES, THAT CONVERSATION

02:10.400 --> 02:12.777
HAS BEEN SEARED PERMANENTLY
IN MY MEMORY.

02:12.820 --> 02:14.572
- [chuckles] SORRY.
- THIS IS NOT ABOUT THAT.

02:14.610 --> 02:16.919
IT'S JUST A CHARITY
FUNDRAISER THING.

02:16.960 --> 02:21.238
YOU KNOW, COCKTAIL DINNER, SOME
FANCY HOUSE OVER IN SEA CLIFF.

02:21.270 --> 02:22.919
THEY SAID I HAD TO BRING
A PLUS-ONE.

02:22.970 --> 02:24.961
NOT A DATE, A PLUS-ONE,

02:25.000 --> 02:27.628
AND YOU SEEM LIKE
THE TYPE OF PLUS-ONE

02:27.660 --> 02:30.788
WHO WOULDN'T DRINK FIVE COSMOS
AND THEN HURL IN THE SHOWER.

02:30.840 --> 02:32.216
- GROSS.
- MM-HMM.

02:32.250 --> 02:33.171
- IS THAT WHAT THAT
LAST GIRL DID, LINCOLN?

02:33.220 --> 02:35.859
- IT WAS THE ONE AFTER LINCOLN,
ACTUALLY.

02:35.910 --> 02:36.899
- JOHNSON?

02:36.940 --> 02:37.759
- HEY, SEE. RIGHT THERE.

02:37.810 --> 02:39.971
YOU JUST MADE
A PRESIDENTIAL JOKE.

02:40.020 --> 02:42.295
NOT EVERYBODY CAN DO
WI'I'I'Y COCKTAIL BANTER.

02:42.330 --> 02:43.490
- HMM.
- YOU SHOULD COME WITH ME.

02:43.540 --> 02:45.531
- MM, WHAT'S IN IT FOR ME?

02:45.570 --> 02:48.198
- WOW. UH, OKAY.

02:48.230 --> 02:52.234
I HAVE A BUDDY IN ADVERTISING
WHO HIRES PHOTOGRAPHERS.

02:52.270 --> 02:55.922
YOU WOULD ENJOY MEETING HIM AND
SOME OTHER FOLKS YOU'LL LIKE.

02:55.960 --> 02:57.336
- OKAY.

02:57.380 --> 02:58.779
- ALL RIGHT.

03:00.590 --> 03:02.797
TALK LATER.

03:05.420 --> 03:07.627
- AND WE'RE IN A BIT OF A HURRY,
SO LET'S MOVE IT NOW.

03:07.670 --> 03:09.319
- HEY, DO YOU GOT A SEC?
- WE'RE NOT LATE.

03:09.360 --> 03:11.351
- UM, IT'S NOT A GOOD TIME.
- I JUST WANTED TO TALK TO YOU,

03:11.390 --> 03:12.903
THAT'S ALL.
- CAN YOU GUYS WAIT IN THE CAR

03:12.950 --> 03:14.463
FOR JUST A SECOND?
- [clears throat]

03:14.500 --> 03:16.730
YOU'RE NOT RETURNING
ANY OF MY EMAILS.

03:16.780 --> 03:19.772
- YOU SHOULDN'T BE EMAILING ME.
- I UNDERSTAND, BUT I'M JUST--

03:19.820 --> 03:22.288
[chuckles]

03:22.340 --> 03:24.786
I WANTED TO APOLOGIZE
FOR THE OTHER DAY, THAT'S ALL.

03:24.820 --> 03:26.742
- I'M NOT GONNA TALK ABOUT IT.
- I KNOW,

03:26.790 --> 03:28.508
BUT I'M GONNA BE
AT THE AUCTION ON FRIDAY,

03:28.550 --> 03:29.574
AND I JUST DON'T WANT IT
TO BE WEIRD, OKAY?

03:29.620 --> 03:31.406
- LISTEN, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU THOUGHT, BUT--

03:31.450 --> 03:33.611
- I THOUGHT THAT I FELT
SOMETHING FROM YOU.

03:33.660 --> 03:36.481
THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.
- I'M MARRIED.

03:46.640 --> 03:51.498
[door opening]
- HANK, I'M HERE.

03:51.540 --> 03:53.701
- HEY. MAD MAX.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

03:53.750 --> 03:56.366
- I TOOK THE LAST THREE PICTURES
THIS MORNING,

03:56.400 --> 03:58.504
AND THEY'RE AMAZING.

03:58.540 --> 04:01.304
WHERE'S THE STUFF?
- WHAT? WHAT STUFF?

04:01.340 --> 04:03.683
- THE STUFF TO DEVELOP
IN THE DARKROOM.

04:03.720 --> 04:04.618
YOU SAID WE'D BE DEVELOPING
MY PICTURES TODAY.

04:04.650 --> 04:07.824
- UH, YEAH,
I GOT TO DO THIS RE-SHOOT.

04:07.860 --> 04:10.033
- OF WHAT, A STUPID PURSE?

04:10.070 --> 04:11.719
- YEAH, WELL,
IT'S NOT A PURSE.

04:11.760 --> 04:15.070
IT'S A CONVERTIBLE CROSS-BODY
BAG SOMETHING, I DON'T KNOW.

04:15.110 --> 04:16.759
- WHO CARES?
- I CARE.

04:16.800 --> 04:19.280
IT'S A BIG CLIENT, YOU KNOW?
GIVE ME THAT FILTER RIGHT THERE.

04:19.320 --> 04:20.696
- NO, YOU SAID THAT WE WOULD
DEVELOP MY PHOTOS TODAY.

04:20.740 --> 04:23.709
YOU PROMISED.
- I KNOW.

04:23.740 --> 04:25.799
LOOK, I GOT THAT,
BUT THIS CAME UP, ALL RIGHT?

04:25.850 --> 04:27.909
- NO!

04:27.950 --> 04:30.919
- MAX, I GOT TO DO THIS.

04:30.960 --> 04:32.882
- YOU SAID THAT WE'D DEVELOP
MY PICTURES TODAY!

04:32.920 --> 04:35.297
- I GET THAT, OKAY?
THIS IS A BIG JOB--

04:35.340 --> 04:36.989
THIS JOB PAYS FOR ME
TO DEVELOP YOUR PICTURES.

04:37.030 --> 04:38.713
- OKAY, FINE, THEN WE WILL
DEVELOP MY PICTURES FIRST

04:38.760 --> 04:41.888
LIKE THE PLAN THAT WE HAD,
AND THEN YOU CAN DO YOURS.

04:41.930 --> 04:43.613
- ALL RIGHT, MAX, LISTEN.
WE'RE NOT DEVELOPING

04:43.660 --> 04:45.992
YOUR PICTURES TODAY, OKAY?
- SO GREAT, SO YOU'RE A LIAR!

04:46.040 --> 04:47.689
- DID YOU--
- YOU LIED!

04:47.730 --> 04:49.379
- HO, DID YOU HEAR
WHAT I SAID?

04:49.420 --> 04:50.978
WE GOT TO DO THE SHOOT.
- NO, YOU PROMISED!

04:51.010 --> 04:52.079
- MAX.

04:52.110 --> 04:54.385
- YOU PROMISED!
- HEY! OH!

04:54.430 --> 04:56.637
- SCREW YOU, HANK!
[screams]

04:56.670 --> 04:59.662
- MAX!

04:59.710 --> 05:00.699
COME ON, MAX!

05:02.710 --> 05:07.363
MAX, HOLD UP!

05:07.410 --> 05:08.502
DAMN IT.

05:09.930 --> 05:11.818
- HEY, BUDDY.
- I'M GOING UPSTAIRS!

05:11.860 --> 05:14.476
- HONEY, WHAT--WHAT IS GOING ON?
- HE'S OKAY, HE GOT A LITTLE--

05:14.520 --> 05:16.966
- HANK IS A LIAR!
- MAX, STOP IT.

05:17.000 --> 05:19.514
- HE'S A LIAR!
- MAX, DON'T CALL PEOPLE A LIAR.

05:19.560 --> 05:21.061
MAX.

05:21.110 --> 05:23.340
I AM SO, SO--WHAT HAPPENED?
- HE GOT--YEAH.

05:23.390 --> 05:24.903
HE GOT UPSET.
HE GOT A LITTLE UPSET.

05:24.940 --> 05:26.623
I DON'T KNOW--

05:26.670 --> 05:27.932
- WHAT WAS THAT ALL ABOUT?
- HE JUST HAD A TANTRUM.

05:27.980 --> 05:29.834
- YEAH, HE WAS AT THE STUDIO.
- UH-HUH.

05:29.880 --> 05:32.974
- HE WANTED TO DO SOMETHING.
I TOLD HIM WE COULDN'T DO IT.

05:33.020 --> 05:35.602
WE HAD TO DO THIS OTHER THING.
YOU KNOW, WE HAD A DEADLINE,

05:35.640 --> 05:36.868
AND HE FLIPPED OUT.
I DON'T--

05:36.920 --> 05:38.672
- OKAY.
- DOES THAT HAPPEN?

05:38.710 --> 05:41.053
- YEAH, SOMETIMES.
- WE'RE WORKING ON STUFF

05:41.090 --> 05:42.671
WITH HIM. I'M SO SORRY.
- HE'S GONNA BE OKAY?

05:42.720 --> 05:43.709
- EVERYTHING IN THE STUDIO'S
OKAY? YOU'RE ALL RIGHT?

05:43.750 --> 05:45.058
- NO, I'M ALL RIGHT.
YEAH, HE'S FAST THOUGH.

05:45.100 --> 05:46.613
THAT'S A FAST KID.
- IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

05:46.650 --> 05:47.469
I GOT TO GO TALK TO HIM.
- I'M SO SORRY, HANK. THANK YOU.

05:47.510 --> 05:48.579
- MAX.
- HE'LL BE OKAY?

05:48.620 --> 05:49.689
- YEAH, HE'LL BE OKAY.

05:49.720 --> 05:54.931
- OOH, MAN, HE'S FAST.
SON OF A BITCH, HE'S FAST.

05:54.970 --> 05:56.790
MAY GOD BLESS
AND KEEP YOU ALWAYS

05:56.830 --> 06:00.414
AND MAY YOUR WISHES
ALL COME TRUE

06:00.460 --> 06:01.791
MAY YOU ALWAYS DO
FOR OTHERS

06:01.840 --> 06:05.071
AND LET OTHERS DO FOR YOU

06:05.120 --> 06:06.803
MAY YOU BUILD A LADDER
TO THE STARS

06:06.840 --> 06:09.491
AND CLIMB ON EVERY RUNG

06:09.540 --> 06:10.734
AND MAY YOU STAY

06:10.780 --> 06:13.886
FOREVER YOUNG

06:13.920 --> 06:17.538
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE RIGHTEOUS

06:17.580 --> 06:18.786
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE TRUE

06:18.820 --> 06:22.130
MAY YOU ALWAYS KNOW
THE TRUTH

06:22.170 --> 06:24.513
AND SEE THE LIGHTS
SURROUNDING YOU

06:24.550 --> 06:26.825
MAY YOU ALWAYS BE
COURAGEOUS

06:26.860 --> 06:28.748
STAND UPRIGHT
AND BE STRONG

06:28.800 --> 06:30.859
AND MAY YOU STAY

06:30.900 --> 06:33.767
FOREVER YOUNG

06:33.800 --> 06:36.041
MAY YOU STAY

06:36.080 --> 06:38.662
FOREVER YOUNG

06:42.090 --> 06:47.949
- [grunting and muttering]

06:47.990 --> 06:50.982
[grunts]

06:51.030 --> 06:53.954
AH. OW. OH!

06:53.990 --> 06:57.926
- BUT IF MY WORD
IS TO BE TRUE

06:57.960 --> 06:59.097
- FINISHED.

06:59.140 --> 07:03.509
- LIFE IS
SOMETHING TO BEHOLD

07:03.560 --> 07:07.553
YES, LIFE IS HARD

07:07.590 --> 07:12.527
COME CELEBRATE

07:12.570 --> 07:17.564
LIFE IS HARD, UH-HUH

07:17.600 --> 07:22.708
UH-HUH-HUH

07:22.750 --> 07:23.819
- HMM.

07:23.850 --> 07:26.091
- OUR LIFE IS ALL

07:26.130 --> 07:31.261
- ZEEK, IT WAS SUCH
A BEAUTIFUL DAY HERE TODAY.

07:31.310 --> 07:33.130
YOU SHOULD'VE SEEN
THE SUNSET LAST NIGHT.

07:33.170 --> 07:34.649
I WISHED YOU WERE HERE.

07:34.690 --> 07:37.796
THERE'S JUST SO MUCH
THAT I WANT TO SHARE WITH YOU.

07:37.830 --> 07:39.513
- THAT SOUNDS GREAT, MILLIE.

07:39.560 --> 07:40.584
- HOW ARE YOU?

07:40.630 --> 07:43.929
- ME?
OH, FINE, FINE, YEAH.

07:43.980 --> 07:46.073
- HOW'S THE OTHER WOMAN?

07:46.120 --> 07:49.078
- UH, WELL,
SHE'S DOING GOOD, YOU KNOW.

07:49.120 --> 07:51.088
I'M WORKING ON HER ALL THE TIME,
AND SLOWLY BUT SURELY--

07:51.120 --> 07:53.156
- WELL, IT WORKED OUT THEN,
DIDN'T IT?

07:53.190 --> 07:56.637
WE'RE BOTH PURSUING
OUR PASSIONS.

07:56.680 --> 07:59.501
- YEAH, IT DID.

07:59.540 --> 08:02.100
- LISTEN, THERE'S A GAL
IN OUR GROUP

08:02.130 --> 08:04.269
WHO'S GOT A LITTLE VILLA
OUTSIDE TUSCANY,

08:04.310 --> 08:07.859
AND SHE INVITED A FEW OF US
TO COME THERE AND PAINT.

08:07.900 --> 08:09.720
IT'S JUST A WONDERFUL
OPPORTUNITY,

08:09.760 --> 08:12.103
AND I DON'T KNOW WHEN
I'D HAVE THE CHANCE AGAIN,

08:12.140 --> 08:17.168
BUT IT WOULD MEAN EXTENDING
MY TRIP A WEEK.

08:17.220 --> 08:21.247
SO I'LL--
I'LL LET YOU THINK ABOUT IT.

08:21.290 --> 08:24.521
- OKAY. YEAH. YEAH.

08:24.570 --> 08:26.083
- YOU'RE SURE I CAN'T JUST
WEAR JEANS?

08:26.120 --> 08:28.680
- NO, YOU CANNOT WEAR JEANS.

08:28.710 --> 08:29.847
- WHY DO YOU HAVE
ALL THESE AWESOME DRESSES?

08:29.880 --> 08:31.916
THIS IS AN AMAZING WARDROBE.
- I THINK THAT WOULD LOOK

08:31.950 --> 08:32.917
REALLY GOOD ON YOU.
- REALLY?

08:32.960 --> 08:33.949
- YEAH.
- ALL RIGHT,

08:33.990 --> 08:34.911
I'LL TRY THAT ONE TOO.
- YEAH.

08:34.960 --> 08:36.951
HEY, UM, WHAT'S THIS GUY'S
LAST NAME AGAIN?

08:36.990 --> 08:38.639
- FLETCHER, CARL FLETCHER.
WHY?

08:38.690 --> 08:39.850
- OKAY.
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

08:39.890 --> 08:40.857
- LOOKIN' HIM UP.
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

08:40.890 --> 08:42.061
- I'M LOOKING HIM UP.
- DON'T LOOK HIM UP.

08:42.100 --> 08:43.749
- WHY NOT?
- BECAUSE

08:43.790 --> 08:45.610
I'M SUPERSTITIOUS ABOUT THAT.

08:45.660 --> 08:48.060
IT'S TACKY AND STALKER-Y.
- [laughs]

08:48.110 --> 08:49.247
- I'M GONNA GO TRY ON
MORE DRESSES.

08:49.280 --> 08:52.215
- IT'S $1,000 A PLATE, OKAY,
SO WE HAVE TO LOOK HIM UP

08:52.250 --> 08:53.899
AND SEE WHAT'S GOING ON
WITH THIS GUY.

08:53.940 --> 08:54.861
AND YOU SHOULD WEAR
THE BLACK ONE.

08:54.910 --> 08:55.877
IT'S GONNA LOOK AMAZING.

08:55.910 --> 08:57.798
- I DON'T WANT TO LOOK AMAZING.
- WHY NOT?

08:57.840 --> 08:59.046
- JASMINE,
IT'S NOT A DATE.

08:59.090 --> 09:02.082
I'M JUST GOING WITH THIS GUY
TO--FOR NETWORKING REASONS,

09:02.120 --> 09:05.055
AND BECAUSE HE ASKED ME
TO BE HIS PLUS-ONE,

09:05.090 --> 09:06.318
AND I THOUGHT, YOU KNOW,
"WHO CARES?"

09:06.370 --> 09:08.645
- UH-HUH. CARL FLETCHER, RIGHT?
THAT'S HIS NAME?

09:08.680 --> 09:10.090
- YEAH.

09:10.130 --> 09:11.051
- IS THIS HIM?
- UGH. IS IT POLICE RECORDS?

09:11.100 --> 09:13.261
CRIMES?
- JUST VERIFY THAT THIS IS HIM.

09:13.310 --> 09:15.756
IS THIS HIM?
- THAT IS--I--VERIFIED, YES.

09:15.790 --> 09:19.135
- OKAY, SO...
"GLOBAL MED WORLD SERVICES

09:19.170 --> 09:22.105
"IS AN INTERNATIONAL NONPROFIT
THAT BUILDS HOSPITALS

09:22.140 --> 09:24.347
AND CLINICS
IN UNDERPRIVILEGED COUNTRIES."

09:24.390 --> 09:25.414
- BUT HE DOESN'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO DO WITH--

09:25.460 --> 09:27.837
- WELL, YEAH, IT IS,
BECAUSE HE IS THE CHAIRMAN

09:27.870 --> 09:32.113
AND EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR OF IT.
HE WENT TO DUKE,

09:32.150 --> 09:33.970
COLUMBIA MED SCHOOL--
- NO, HE DIDN'T.

09:34.020 --> 09:36.329
- AND HE IS BOARD CERTIFIED
IN NEONATOLOGY.

09:36.360 --> 09:38.180
- YOU'VE GOT TO BE KIDDING ME.
- NO, HE--

09:38.230 --> 09:41.154
- HE'S A DOCTOR?
- AND HE SAVES BABIES.

09:41.200 --> 09:43.122
- UH, THIS SOUNDS LIKE
A MAJOR EVENING.

09:45.370 --> 09:47.122
- I BE'I'I'ER TRY THE BLACK ONE.
- YOU SHOULD WEAR THE BLACK ONE,

09:47.170 --> 09:48.853
YEAH. YEAH.
- [chuckles] GOD.

09:48.890 --> 09:51.097
- YEAH.

09:58.730 --> 10:02.314
- EXCUSE ME, HANK. HI.
- OH, HEY. HOW'S IT GOING?

10:02.360 --> 10:04.760
- IT'S GOING ALL RIGHT.
LISTEN, I WANTED TO APOLOGIZE

10:04.810 --> 10:07.768
TO YOU FOR MAX'S BLOWUP
THE OTHER DAY.

10:07.810 --> 10:08.799
I'M SORRY ABOUT THAT.
- YEAH, NO, THAT'S OKAY.

10:08.840 --> 10:12.219
HOW IS HE--HE'S OKAY?
IS HE MAD AT ME STILL?

10:12.260 --> 10:13.909
- YEAH.
- YEAH.

10:13.950 --> 10:15.770
- UNFORTUNATELY,
MAX CAN BE KIND OF STUBBORN.

10:15.820 --> 10:17.299
BUT YOU HANDLED THE SITUATION
REALLY WELL, SO--

10:17.340 --> 10:18.227
- YEAH, HE--
BUT HE DOES THAT, HUH?

10:18.270 --> 10:20.363
- YEAH.
- YEAH.

10:20.410 --> 10:22.162
- HE GOT IT INTO HIS HEAD
THAT YOU LIED TO HIM,

10:22.200 --> 10:23.827
WHICH I'M SURE
ISN'T TRUE, AND--

10:23.860 --> 10:25.373
- [sighs] YEAH, NO, I--
- IT'S TYPICAL OF MAX

10:25.410 --> 10:26.820
THAT HE CAN'T LET THINGS GO.

10:26.860 --> 10:27.963
SO IT'S IRRATIONAL,
IT'S FRUSTRATING...

10:28.000 --> 10:29.752
- YEAH, NO, I KNOW.
- BUT I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW,

10:29.800 --> 10:30.869
DON'T TAKE IT PERSONALLY.

10:30.900 --> 10:31.969
- NO, I DON'T.
I MEAN, YOU KNOW,

10:32.010 --> 10:36.720
TO BE HONEST, I DID
BREAK A PROMISE TO HIM, SO--

10:36.770 --> 10:38.351
- WELL, THAT HAPPENS.
- YEAH.

10:38.390 --> 10:40.187
- AND HE NEEDS TO LEARN
HOW TO DEAL WITH THAT.

10:40.220 --> 10:41.972
- YEAH.
- AND I BROUGHT YOU

10:42.020 --> 10:42.975
THIS BOOK
ON ASPERGER'S SYNDROME.

10:43.020 --> 10:44.112
I DON'T KNOW IF YOU HAVE TIME
TO READ IT,

10:44.160 --> 10:46.185
BUT IT MIGHT HELP UNDERSTAND
MAX A LITTLE BIT BE'I'I'ER,

10:46.230 --> 10:49.256
BECAUSE WE REALLY WANT THIS
TO WORK OUT HERE.

10:49.300 --> 10:51.052
I MEAN, WE LOVE
THAT HE COMES HERE.

10:51.090 --> 10:52.125
IT'S BEEN REALLY GOOD FOR HIM.
- YEAH, NO, I KNOW, I KNOW.

10:52.160 --> 10:53.263
RELAX.
- OKAY.

10:53.300 --> 10:55.928
I MEAN, I'M--I LIKE HIM.
I LIKE THE KID,

10:55.960 --> 10:57.439
SO IT'S NOT THAT COMPLICATED,
REALLY.

10:57.480 --> 10:58.549
- OKAY, GOOD.
- YEAH.

10:58.580 --> 11:00.332
IF YOU WANT TO, HOPEFULLY,
IT'LL BE OF SOME HELP.

11:00.380 --> 11:03.133
- YEAH, SURE.
- THIS IS COOL.

11:03.170 --> 11:05.821
HEY, LOOK AT THAT.
LONDON PUMPS.

11:05.870 --> 11:07.349
- YEAH.
IT'S WEIRD THAT YOU KNOW THAT.

11:07.390 --> 11:10.382
- OH.
- IT'S GOT TO GO BACK, THOUGH.

11:10.420 --> 11:12.172
- OH, YEAH. OH, BOY.
- I GO'I'I'A DO THE THING, YEAH.

11:12.220 --> 11:13.835
- YEP, SURE. OF COURSE.
- YEAH, NO, THAT'S--

11:13.880 --> 11:15.006
- ALL RIGHT, YOU'RE WORKING.
I'M GONNA GO.

11:15.050 --> 11:16.972
- I MEAN, I JUST--I SET THAT UP.
- OKAY, IF YOU HAVE TIME

11:17.020 --> 11:18.840
FOR THE BOOK, GREAT. ALL RIGHT.
- YEAH, YEAH,

11:18.880 --> 11:20.256
I'LL TAKE A LOOK INTO THAT,
BUT--YOU KNOW,

11:20.300 --> 11:23.053
SAY HELLO TO HIM,
OR SOMETHING.

11:23.090 --> 11:23.943
- OKAY.
- YEAH.

11:27.960 --> 11:30.884
- HI.

11:37.210 --> 11:39.895
EH...

11:39.940 --> 11:42.761
- PRETI'Y STUPID, HUH?

11:42.800 --> 11:44.381
EVERYBODY IN HERE
IS OLDER THAN DIRT.

11:44.420 --> 11:46.832
YOU'D THINK THEY'D MAKE
THE PRINT BIGGER.

11:46.870 --> 11:49.213
- YEAH.
- THE B.L.T.'S GOOD.

11:49.260 --> 11:52.775
- UH-HUH.
- IT'S NOT ON THE MENU,

11:52.810 --> 11:54.323
BUT DORIS WILL MAKE IT FOR YOU
IF YOU ASK HER.

11:54.360 --> 11:58.228
WON'T YOU, DORIS?

11:58.260 --> 12:00.262
- WANT SOME COFFEE, HON?

12:00.300 --> 12:04.236
- UH, NO, THANK YOU.
I'D JUST LIKE A BEER AND, UM...

12:04.270 --> 12:07.068
I'LL TRY THE TURKEY MEATLOAF.

12:07.100 --> 12:09.239
THANKS.
- HOW ABOUT THOSE NINERS?

12:09.280 --> 12:10.781
- YEAH, HOW ABOUT 'EM?

12:10.830 --> 12:12.889
- PEOPLE ARE GONNA BE TALKING
ABOUT THIS SEASON

12:12.930 --> 12:14.409
FOR A LONG TIME.
- YEAH.

12:14.450 --> 12:18.102
- OR ARE YOU A RAIDERS FAN?

12:18.150 --> 12:20.835
- UH, SIR, YOU KNOW,
I DON'T WANT TO BE RUDE,

12:20.870 --> 12:23.282
BUT I DON'T WANT TO CHITCHAT.

12:23.320 --> 12:26.289
I JUST WANT TO EAT MY DINNER,
HAVE MY BEER,

12:26.330 --> 12:28.423
AND WORK ON MY CROSSWORD,
IF YOU DON'T MIND.

12:28.470 --> 12:30.119
- SURE.
- THANKS.

12:30.160 --> 12:32.219
- I GOT YOU.

12:32.260 --> 12:34.262
WORKING ON THAT
ALZHEIMER'S THING.

12:34.300 --> 12:36.052
- NO, I DON'T HAVE
ALZHEIMER'S.

12:36.100 --> 12:38.921
- YOU WON'T IF YOU KEEP DOING
THAT CROSSWORD.

12:38.960 --> 12:40.996
GOOD FOR YOU.

12:41.030 --> 12:43.407
CREEPS UP ON YOU,
YOU KNOW.

12:43.450 --> 12:45.133
YOU DON'T KNOW YOU'RE GETTING
ALZHEIMER'S,

12:45.170 --> 12:47.274
CAUSE YOU'VE GOT ALZHEIMER'S.

12:47.310 --> 12:50.859
YOU DON'T...FORGET...
WHAT YOU FORMERLY KNEW.

12:50.900 --> 12:52.868
- YOU GOT ANY FRIENDS?

12:52.910 --> 12:55.242
- WELL, I WASN'T TRYING TO GET
FRESH WITH YOU OR ANYTHING.

12:55.290 --> 12:57.520
- NO, I DIDN'T--
- JUST--

12:57.560 --> 12:59.255
- GOD.
- WHAT A PUTZ.

12:59.290 --> 13:01.804
- WHAT?
- NOTHING.

13:02.920 --> 13:04.182
- JULES.
- HI.

13:04.230 --> 13:05.538
- WHAT'S GOING ON?
- I HAVE A FAVOR TO ASK YOU,

13:05.570 --> 13:07.504
AND I WAS IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD,
SO I THOUGHT I'D JUST COME ASK.

13:07.540 --> 13:11.408
- COME ON IN. HAVE A SEAT.
- OKAY, UM,

13:11.440 --> 13:13.886
SO TOMORROW NIGHT, YOU KNOW
WE HAVE THE AUCTION AT SYCAMORE?

13:13.930 --> 13:16.956
- YEAH, WE'RE WATCHING
JABBAR AND AIDA FOR CROSBY.

13:17.000 --> 13:18.922
- NO. NEVER MIND THEN.
- WHAT?

13:18.970 --> 13:20.585
- I WAS GONNA ASK IF VICTOR
AND SYDNEY COULD COME OVER.

13:20.620 --> 13:22.201
- OF COURSE.
- REALLY?

13:22.240 --> 13:23.138
- YEAH, WE'LL JUST HAVE
A BIG SLEEPOVER.

13:23.180 --> 13:24.442
- ALL OF THEM?
- YOU AND JOEL CAN HAVE

13:24.490 --> 13:25.934
A NIGHT OUT.

13:25.970 --> 13:28.450
- YEP.
[chuckles]

13:28.490 --> 13:30.173
- YOU ALL RIGHT?

13:30.220 --> 13:31.903
- YEAH. YEAH.

13:31.940 --> 13:33.498
- JULIA.
- NO, IT'S FINE.

13:33.530 --> 13:34.383
- JULIA.
- ADAM.

13:34.430 --> 13:36.569
- SOMETHING'S GOING ON.
LOOK AT ME.

13:36.600 --> 13:41.606
- IT'S--IT'S--IT'S NOT...

13:41.640 --> 13:43.437
BEEN GOING WELL...

13:43.470 --> 13:45.574
BETWEEN JOEL AND I.

13:46.680 --> 13:49.501
_- WHAT'S GOING ON?
- [Sighs] THERE'S THIS GUY.

13:49.550 --> 13:51.609
NO. NO, NO, NO.
- THERE'S A GUY?

13:53.340 --> 13:55.444
THERE'S THIS GUY WHO'S A DAD
AT THE SCHOOL,

13:55.480 --> 13:58.108
AND WE'RE ON THE SAME VOLUNTEER
COMMITTEE SO, YOU KNOW,

13:58.140 --> 14:00.654
WE'VE BEEN SPENDING A BUNCH
OF TIME TOGETHER AT THAT,

14:00.700 --> 14:04.352
AND WE'VE BECOME FRIENDS,
AND I DID NOT INTEND

14:04.390 --> 14:06.426
FOR ANYTHING TO HAPPEN,
BUT...

14:06.460 --> 14:11.250
WE WERE TALKING
THE OTHER DAY,

14:11.290 --> 14:12.871
AND--AND. ..
- OKAY.

14:12.920 --> 14:14.876
- HE KISSED ME.

14:14.920 --> 14:18.128
- HE JUST KISSED YOU?
- YEAH.

14:18.160 --> 14:20.025
- LOOK, THIS SORT OF THING
HAPPENS.

14:20.060 --> 14:21.948
I MEAN, BELIEVE IT OR NOT,
IT HAPPENED TO ME.

14:21.990 --> 14:24.060
THIS ASSISTANT WE HAD
AT THE LUNCHEONE'ITE, RACHEL,

14:24.100 --> 14:26.921
JUST KISSED ME,
AND I IMMEDIATELY TOLD CHRISTINA

14:26.960 --> 14:30.964
ABOUT IT, AND WE WORKED IT OUT.
YOU'LL BE FINE.

14:31.000 --> 14:33.002
- YOU DIDN'T KISS HER BACK?

14:33.040 --> 14:35.179
- NO, OF COURSE NOT.
- OKAY.

14:35.210 --> 14:38.418
- JULIA?
- GOOD. WELL, I DON'T--

14:38.460 --> 14:42.214
I DON'T KNOW, MAYBE THIS IS--
MAYBE THIS IS DIFFERENT.

14:46.470 --> 14:48.256
- DO YOU HAVE FEELINGS
FOR THIS GUY?

14:48.300 --> 14:51.508
- I DON'T KNOW. NO.

14:51.540 --> 14:52.359
- OKAY.

14:52.400 --> 14:57.406
- IT'S JUST BEEN...

14:57.440 --> 15:00.648
SO HARD WITH JOEL AND I.

15:00.690 --> 15:03.898
WE CANNOT GET
ON THE SAME PAGE AT ALL.

15:06.730 --> 15:11.975
ADAM, HE DOESN'T...
LOOK AT ME...

15:15.050 --> 15:18.702
AND SO--AND JUST--
HE SEES ME,

15:18.740 --> 15:21.732
YOU KNOW?
- OKAY. YEAH.

15:21.780 --> 15:23.429
HEY, JULIA.
- YEAH?

15:23.470 --> 15:25.631
- LISTEN TO ME, OKAY?
WHATEVER IS FEELING GOOD

15:25.680 --> 15:30.333
RIGHT NOW ABOUT ED
IS JUST RELATED

15:30.370 --> 15:32.406
TO HOW BAD THINGS ARE FEELING
WITH JOEL, ALL RIGHT,

15:32.440 --> 15:35.091
AND IT IS NOT WORTH IT.
IT'S NOT ABOUT HIM.

15:35.140 --> 15:36.368
THIS IS ABOUT YOU AND JOEL,
AND YOU'VE GOT TO FOCUS

15:36.410 --> 15:38.378
ON YOUR MARRIAGE.

15:38.420 --> 15:40.968
OKAY? IT'S ABOUT YOU.
IT'S ABOUT YOUR FAMILY.

15:41.000 --> 15:43.070
IT'S NOT WORTH IT, OKAY?
YOU GOT TO GET THIS GUY

15:43.110 --> 15:44.759
OUT OF YOUR LIFE
AND FORGET ABOUT HIM.

15:44.800 --> 15:46.973
FIGURE YOUR STUFF OUT
WITH JOEL, OKAY?

15:47.010 --> 15:48.978
IF YOU GUYS NEED TO GO
TALK TO SOMEBODY,

15:49.010 --> 15:50.284
YOU CAN DO--
HAVE YOU DONE THAT?

15:50.320 --> 15:52.379
- WERE TALKING ABOUT--
WE WERE TRYING TO.

15:52.430 --> 15:54.079
- OKAY, ALL RIGHT.
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY, ALL RIGHT?

15:54.120 --> 15:55.326
- OKAY.
- ALL RIGHT?

15:55.360 --> 15:56.327
YOU DIDN'T DO ANYTHING WRONG.

15:56.360 --> 15:58.533
YOU DIDN'T DO ANYTHING WRONG.
YOU'RE OKAY.

15:58.570 --> 15:59.605
ALL RIGHT?
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

15:59.640 --> 16:02.461
- OH, ADAM, THANK YOU.
- YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

16:02.510 --> 16:04.671
- [sighs]
- IT'S ALL RIGHT.

16:10.030 --> 16:13.272
[car engine rewing
in video game]

16:13.310 --> 16:17.007
- HEY.
- OH, WOW, HAND DELIVER--

16:17.040 --> 16:18.655
WOW, LOOK AT THAT BASKET.

16:18.700 --> 16:21.282
- THAT WAS ALL AMBER.
- THAT IS AMAZING.

16:21.320 --> 16:23.379
- I HAD NOTHING TO DO WITH IT.
- JUST REALLY TOP NOTCH.

16:23.430 --> 16:25.352
- I DON'T KNOW WHAT SHE PUT
IN THERE--THAT THING'S SO HEAW.

16:25.390 --> 16:26.766
- HEY, UNCLE ADAM.
- JABBAR, WHAT IS GOING ON?

16:26.810 --> 16:28.323
- NOTHING.
- THAT IS A QUALITY BASKET.

16:28.360 --> 16:29.804
- CAN WE HAVE PIZZA TONIGHT?

16:29.850 --> 16:31.636
- WHAT TOPPINGS AND HOW MANY?
OKAY, THIS IS

16:31.680 --> 16:33.602
THE BRAVERMAN SLEEPOVER
EXT RAVAGANZA OF THE YEAR.

16:33.640 --> 16:34.777
- YES.
- HEY, CAN YOU GRAB

16:34.820 --> 16:36.219
YOUR SLEEPING BAG
AND ALL YOUR PARTY GEAR?

16:36.270 --> 16:37.669
I JUST WANT TO TALK TO YOUR DAD
FOR A SECOND.

16:37.720 --> 16:39.335
- OKAY.
- THANKS.

16:39.370 --> 16:41.474
- YOU'RE GOING CLARK GRISWOLD
ON THIS SLEEPOVER, HUH?

16:41.510 --> 16:43.330
- YEAH.

16:43.380 --> 16:46.235
YOU KNOW ED BROOKS?
- ED WHO?

16:46.280 --> 16:49.204
- ED BROOKS.
HE'S A DAD AT SYCAMORE.

16:49.240 --> 16:51.037
- OH, ED BROOKS.
YEAH, YEAH.

16:51.070 --> 16:52.765
HE'S ON THE GREEN POLICE
COMMITTEE WITH JULIA.

16:52.800 --> 16:54.313
- EXACTLY, SO DID SHE
TALK TO YOU ABOUT HIM?

16:54.350 --> 16:56.033
- WHAT ABOUT HIM?

16:56.080 --> 16:58.594
- HE'S RECENTLY SEPARATED.
HE AND JULIA HAVE BEEN

16:58.630 --> 17:00.564
SPENDING SOME TIME TOGETHER,
HAD SOME CONVERSATIONS,

17:00.600 --> 17:02.420
AND HE KISSED HER.

17:02.460 --> 17:05.179
- ED BROOKS?
- YEAH.

17:05.230 --> 17:07.494
- PUDGY ED BROOKS KISSED JULIA?
- KISSED OUR SISTER, YES.

17:07.540 --> 17:10.191
BUT IT'S NOT--
- DOES JOEL KNOW?

17:10.230 --> 17:11.709
- NO.
IT'S COMPLICATED, BECAUSE--

17:11.750 --> 17:14.787
LOOK, JULIA'S BEEN HAVING
SOME PROBLEMS WITH JOEL.

17:14.820 --> 17:16.333
- WHAT KIND OF PROBLEMS?
- I DON'T KNOW.

17:16.380 --> 17:18.132
BUT SHE CAME OVER TO THE HOUSE

17:18.170 --> 17:19.376
AND SHE STARTED
TO TELL ME ABOUT IT,

17:19.410 --> 17:21.230
AND SHE GOT REALLY UPSET.

17:21.280 --> 17:23.726
SO ED IS GONNA BE
AT THIS AUCTION.

17:23.760 --> 17:26.240
I JUST WANT YOU TO BE LOOKING
OUT FOR OUR BABY SISTER, OKAY?

17:26.280 --> 17:29.101
MAKE SURE NOTHING HAPPENS
AND...

17:29.150 --> 17:30.071
- ROGER.
- MAKE SURE HE KEEPS

17:30.110 --> 17:32.112
HIS DISTANCE, ALL RIGHT?

17:32.150 --> 17:33.492
- I ACCEPT.
- ALL RIGHT.

17:33.530 --> 17:35.521
JUST MAKE SURE YOU GOT HER BACK.
- I'LL BE ON THIS GUY

17:35.570 --> 17:37.458
LIKE A HAWK. I'LL--
- DON'T MAKE IT OBVIOUS.

17:37.500 --> 17:38.535
JUST MAKE SURE YOU HAVE
HER BACK, THAT'S ALL I'M ASKING.

17:38.570 --> 17:40.390
- SUBTLE, BUT DIRECT.
- EXACTLY.

17:40.430 --> 17:43.081
- WE DO WANT TO SEND
A SIGNAL, YEAH?

17:43.130 --> 17:44.631
- OH, YEAH.
- OKAY, GOOD.

17:44.680 --> 17:46.432
- YEAH. JABBAR, YOU READY?
- YEAH.

17:46.470 --> 17:49.542
- OH, MY GOD.
THE SUN, YES.

17:49.580 --> 17:52.196
- I TAKE IT
YOU MISS CALIFORNIA?

17:52.240 --> 17:54.128
- ARE YOU KIDDING?

17:54.170 --> 17:56.786
MY ENTIRE WARDROBE IN BOSTON
CONSISTS OF PARKAS AND BOOTS.

17:56.830 --> 17:58.821
IT'S THE COLDEST PLACE
ON EARTH.

17:58.870 --> 18:00.246
- SO TELL ME HOW YOU GUYS MET.

18:00.280 --> 18:02.453
_ UM--

18:02.490 --> 18:05.459
- UH, W-WE WENT
TO HIGH SCHOOL TOGETHER.

18:05.490 --> 18:06.764
- YEAH.

18:06.800 --> 18:09.257
- YEAH, BUT, LIKE,
HOW'D YOU "MEET" MEET?

18:09.290 --> 18:12.327
- IT WAS ENGLISH, I THINK.
- YEAH, I THINK ENGLISH CLASS,

18:12.360 --> 18:13.497
YEAH.
- YEAH.

18:13.540 --> 18:15.804
- ENGLISH?
OH, MY GOD, THAT SO BORING.

18:15.850 --> 18:19.320
I MET MY HIGH SCHOOL BOYFRIEND
AT THIS DIRTY PROJECTOR SHOW.

18:19.370 --> 18:21.918
HE WAS, LIKE, A HUGE MUSIC NERD
LIKE DREW.

18:21.960 --> 18:24.542
- OH. WELL, I WOULDN'T SAY
I'M A MUSIC NERD.

18:24.580 --> 18:27.469
- [laughing] NO, I'M KIDDING.
I LOVE YOUR MUSIC.

18:27.520 --> 18:33.129
JUST ONE OF THE REASONS WHY
WE LOVE HIM, HUH?

18:33.180 --> 18:35.694
SO WHAT SHOULD WE DO TONIGHT?

19:16.500 --> 19:19.833
[knocking at the door]

19:19.880 --> 19:21.359
- HI.
- LISTEN, DO I--

19:21.400 --> 19:23.800
DO I NOT PICK UP ON CUES?
- WHAT?

19:23.850 --> 19:25.568
- SOCIAL CUES,
YOU KNOW, LIKE MAX.

19:25.610 --> 19:27.601
- I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

19:27.640 --> 19:29.574
- [sighs]
I NEED SOMETHING.

19:29.610 --> 19:31.669
I GOT TO--I DIDN'T SLEEP.
I DIDN'T SLEEP AT ALL.

19:31.720 --> 19:33.995
I'VE BEEN UP ALL NIGHT.
I NEED ALCOHOL,

19:34.030 --> 19:35.782
ANYTHING WITH ALCOHOL IN IT.
- OKAY.

19:35.820 --> 19:36.718
- YOU DON'T GOT NOTHING.
NOTHING.

19:36.760 --> 19:38.512
NOT A BEER, NOT ONE SINGLE BEER.
- I DO.

19:38.550 --> 19:39.960
- I DON'T HAVE BEER,
BUT HOLD ON.

19:40.000 --> 19:41.444
I'LL POUR YOU SOMETHING.
- WHAT KIND OF PLACE IS THIS?

19:41.490 --> 19:42.206
- WHAT IS THAT BOOK?
- HOW DO YOU NOT HAVE BEER?

19:42.250 --> 19:43.649
- WHAT IS GOING ON?
- [sighs]

19:43.690 --> 19:45.419
MAX, HE FLIPPED OUT.

19:45.460 --> 19:47.928
HE HAD A MELTDOWN
THE OTHER DAY, YOU KNOW?

19:47.970 --> 19:48.971
- OKAY.
- AND EVEN THAT--

19:49.010 --> 19:53.526
SEE, EVEN THAT--
I USED TO HAVE HUGE MELTDOWNS

19:53.570 --> 19:55.424
ALL THE TIME, ALL THE TIME.
ONCE THIS KID--

19:55.470 --> 19:56.664
- WHEN?
- THIS KID CHEATED ME

19:56.710 --> 19:59.702
TRADING BASEBALL CARDS,
AND I FLIPPED OUT.

19:59.750 --> 20:00.637
I MEAN, I FLIPPED THE HELL OUT
ON THIS KID.

20:00.680 --> 20:02.739
- WHAT'S THAT BOOK?
WHAT IS HAPPENING?

20:02.780 --> 20:04.919
- IT WAS NOTHING.
I WAS READING THIS BOOK FOR MAX.

20:04.960 --> 20:07.713
I'M READING IT FOR THE KID,
AND THEN ALL OF A SUDDEN,

20:07.750 --> 20:09.433
I'M NOT READING
ABOUT THE KID ANYMORE.

20:09.480 --> 20:11.926
I'M READING ABOUT ME.
THIS BOOK IS DESCRIBING ME.

20:11.960 --> 20:13.234
- WHERE?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

20:13.280 --> 20:15.726
- LOOK AT THIS.

20:15.760 --> 20:17.967
RIGHT THERE, "DIFFICULTY
EXPRESSING EMOTIONS."

20:18.000 --> 20:19.695
- HANK, THAT EVERY MAN I KNOW.
- YEAH. HERE.

20:19.730 --> 20:22.244
"INSENSITIVE TO NONVERBAL CUES
OF OTHERS."

20:22.290 --> 20:23.109
"TAKING DIRECTIONS LITERALLY."

20:23.150 --> 20:24.697
"FAILURE TO READ
BETWEEN THE LINES."

20:24.740 --> 20:26.833
"UNCOMFORTABLE
WITH THE EYE CONTACT,"

20:26.880 --> 20:28.836
EVERYTHING.
CHECK, CHECK, CHECK.

20:28.880 --> 20:30.734
YOU KNOW, I'M SEEING MY LIFE
HERE, I'M SEEING MY LIFE.

20:30.780 --> 20:32.919
I'M SEEING EVERYTHING,
THE WHOLE THING,

20:32.950 --> 20:35.703
WHY STUFF HAPPENS.
I'M SEEING MY WIFE.

20:35.750 --> 20:38.469
YOU KNOW, MY WIFE--
I ALWAYS THOUGHT SHE WAS

20:38.510 --> 20:43.334
THIS ROYAL BITCH, BUT YEAH,
WHAT IF IT'S ME ALL ALONG?

20:43.380 --> 20:44.608
WHAT IF SHE CAN'T DEAL WITH ME
BECAUSE OF THIS,

20:44.650 --> 20:47.539
BECAUSE OF ME,
'CAUSE OF WHO I AM,

20:47.590 --> 20:49.478
BECAUSE--WHAT IF THIS IS
THE REASON

20:49.520 --> 20:51.306
I'M LOSING
ALL THOSE BIG JOBS,

20:51.350 --> 20:55.343
OR MY DAUGHTER
DOESN'T WANT TO SEE ME,

20:55.390 --> 20:59.247
OR YOU, YOU KNOW?
YOU--

21:08.680 --> 21:12.776
YOU GOING ON A DATE
OR SOMETHING?

21:12.820 --> 21:16.438
- KIND OF.

21:16.480 --> 21:18.471
- SEE? I MISSED ANOTHER CUE.
- NO, NO. IT'S--

21:18.510 --> 21:19.954
I'M JUST--
I'M GOING TO A THING.

21:20.000 --> 21:21.376
I'M A PLUS-ONE.
- THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

21:21.410 --> 21:23.787
YOU DON'T GOT TO PROTECT
MY FEELINGS OR ANYTHING.

21:23.830 --> 21:28.517
I GO ON DATES,
JUST SO YOU KNOW.

21:28.560 --> 21:29.868
NO WONDER I LIKE THIS KID,
THOUGH.

21:29.900 --> 21:33.688
I MEAN, THAT'S--IT'S--
I'M JUST LIKE HIM, RIGHT?

21:34.670 --> 21:37.047
I'M JUST LIKE MAX.

21:37.080 --> 21:39.799
- I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE A LITTLE.

21:39.850 --> 21:43.741
IF YOU ARE, YOU'RE DOING GREAT.
I MEAN, YOU HAVE A--

21:43.780 --> 21:47.534
YOU'RE REALLY TALENTED AND
YOU'VE RAISED A BEAUTIFUL KID,

21:47.580 --> 21:50.708
AND NO KID AT THAT AGE
WANTS TO TALK TO THEIR PARENTS,

21:50.750 --> 21:54.538
YOU KNOW?
