THE OFFICIAL CAMPAIGN
PHOTOGRAPH ER

25:22.070 --> 25:23.059
FOR A MAYORAL CANDIDATE.

25:23.100 --> 25:28.276
- YES. [laughs]
MY SISTER-IN-LAW, KRISTINA,

25:28.310 --> 25:34.169
BUT SHE, UM--UH--I--

25:34.220 --> 25:36.108
IT WAS MY SISTER-IN-LAW.
- MM-HMM.

25:36.150 --> 25:39.870
- HER CAMPAIGN.
SORRY, I'M DISTRACT ED

25:39.910 --> 25:41.662
BY THE VERY ATTRACTIVE
BUSINESSPEOPLE

25:41.710 --> 25:43.154
HERE AT THIS PARTY.
[both laughing]

25:43.190 --> 25:46.364
- TWO MORE YEARS OF THIS, RIGHT?
THEN WE'RE DONE?

25:46.400 --> 25:48.288
- HOPEFULLY.
HOPEFULLY, IT DOESN'T GET WORSE

25:48.330 --> 25:49.809
AI-TER MIDDLE SCHOOL.

25:49.850 --> 25:52.614
- CAN'T GET ME TO THE BAR
FAST ENOUGH.

25:52.650 --> 25:55.164
- LET'S, UM, GO CHECK OUT
THE REST OF THE BASKETS

25:55.200 --> 25:57.998
OVER HERE.
- I JUST WANT TO GRAB A DRINK.

25:58.030 --> 26:01.067
- I KNOW.
LET'S GET IT OVER WITH, THOUGH.

26:01.110 --> 26:03.965
GOT TO KNOW WHAT'S THERE.

26:08.110 --> 26:10.624
- OH.
- OH, SARAH'S EXHIBIT.

26:10.670 --> 26:12.592
- YEAH.

26:12.640 --> 26:15.598
- OH!
OH, THIS WON'T DO.

26:15.640 --> 26:17.358
- NO ONE'S BID ON ANYTHING YET.

26:17.400 --> 26:19.800
- WELL, I HAVE AN IDEA.
- WHAT?

26:19.850 --> 26:21.886
WHO'S ED BROOKS?

26:21.920 --> 26:23.148
- OH, HE'S
A VERY GENEROUS MAN.

26:23.200 --> 26:26.021
"PERSON OF INTEREST,"
WE'LL CALL HIM.

26:26.060 --> 26:27.948
- [laughs]

26:31.140 --> 26:33.779
- SPA PACKAGE, HUH?
- OH.

26:33.830 --> 26:34.728
- NO, IT'S--
- REALLY? I CAN'T EVEN

26:34.760 --> 26:37.172
TALK TO YOU ABOUT
YOUR SILENT AUCTION NOW?

26:37.210 --> 26:40.008
- ED, I CAN--
I CAN SMELL ALCOHOL ON YOU.

26:40.040 --> 26:41.007
- JUST TALK TO ME
FOR ONE MINUTE.

26:41.040 --> 26:43.793
DO YOU REALIZE
THAT IT'S ONLY TAKEN COLLEEN

26:43.840 --> 26:45.319
FOUR WEEKS TO TURN
THE ENTIRE SCHOOL AGAINST ME?

26:45.360 --> 26:49.399
EVERYBODY HATES ME HERE.
- OKAY, I'M--I'M NOT GONNA--

26:49.430 --> 26:51.182
- SHE CLEARLY BID
ON THE NAPA TRIP

26:51.230 --> 26:53.425
AFTER THE BIDDING WAS CLOSED.
- OKAY.

26:53.470 --> 26:55.392
- THERE ARE RULES IN PLACE...
- YOU MIGHT BE BEING DRAMATIC.

26:55.440 --> 26:57.089
- AT THIS EVENT.

26:57.130 --> 26:59.223
IF THE RULES ARE NOT FOLLOWED,
IT IS CHAOS.

26:59.270 --> 27:01.921
- [low conversation]

27:01.960 --> 27:04.929
THAT HAS EVER EXISTED.
- WHY DON'T YOU GO HOME, OKAY?

27:04.960 --> 27:06.962
'CAUSE YOU'RE UPSET
ABOUT COLLEEN, AND YOU'RE--

27:07.000 --> 27:08.228
- NO, I'M NOT--
I'M UPSET ABOUT YOU.

27:08.280 --> 27:10.168
- NO, YOU'RE NOT.

27:10.210 --> 27:11.279
- DON'T TELL ME
WHAT I'M UPSET ABOUT.

27:11.310 --> 27:14.450
- I-I-I CAN'T. I'M SORRY, ED.
- COME ON--JULIA--

27:14.490 --> 27:17.175
- THAT YOU ARE PLAYING
FAST AND LOOSE--

27:17.220 --> 27:18.938
- CAN YOU EXCUSE ME
FOR ONE SECOND?

27:18.980 --> 27:21.039
YOU CAN YELL AT ME
RIGHT WHEN I GET BACK, OKAY?

27:21.080 --> 27:22.354
- ED, I DON'T--
- EVERYTHING OKAY?

27:22.390 --> 27:24.142
- YEAH, IT'S FINE.
- YEAH, JOEL.

27:24.190 --> 27:26.351
WHAT'S UP?
- ED IS GOING HOME.

27:26.400 --> 27:27.674
- YOUR WIFE IS AWESOME.
- SHE IS, YEAH.

27:27.710 --> 27:29.223
AND IT LOOKS LIKE SHE DOESN'T
WANT TO TALK TO YOU RIGHT NOW.

27:29.260 --> 27:31.672
- WE'RE TOTALLY CHILL.
WE'RE JUST--

27:31.710 --> 27:33.849
DID YOU AUCTION ON ANYTHING?
DID YOU BUY ANYTHING?

27:33.890 --> 27:34.640
'CAUSE THERE IS
SOME GOOD STUFF HERE.

27:34.680 --> 27:35.851
- OKAY.
- LET'S CALL IT A NIGHT.

27:35.890 --> 27:36.879
- NO, I'M GOOD,
I'M HAVING FUN.

27:36.930 --> 27:38.409
I'M NOT READY TO CALL ANY--
- NO, YOU'RE NOT.

27:38.440 --> 27:39.475
YOU'RE DRUNK,
AND YOU'RE BOTHERING MY WIFE.

27:39.510 --> 27:41.785
- I'M NOT BOTHERING HER.
YOU NEED TO JUST RELAX.

27:41.830 --> 27:42.785
TRUST ME.
- DON'T TOUCH ME!

27:42.830 --> 27:44.138
- HEY! WHOA!
[people gasping]

27:44.170 --> 27:46.206
- JOEL, JOEL, JOEL, JOEL, JOEL.
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

27:46.250 --> 27:47.797
- DUDE, WHAT IS YOUR PROBLEM?

27:47.830 --> 27:50.219
- STAY AWAY FROM MY WIFE.

27:50.250 --> 27:52.218
- [chuckles]
- OKAY.

27:52.250 --> 27:56.072
OKAY.
ALL RIGHT, EVERYTHING'S GOOD.

27:56.120 --> 27:58.350
NOT A BIG DEAL.
EVERYONE'S HORSING AROUND.

27:58.400 --> 28:01.016
GO BACK TO THE PARTY.
STILL BIDDING HERE.

28:01.050 --> 28:03.189
COME ON, LET'S GO.
LET'S GET YOU OUT OF HERE.

28:09.170 --> 28:12.196
- EIGHT BALL, SIDE POCKET.
- YOU WISH.

28:12.240 --> 28:14.856
- RATHER SIMPLE.

28:16.480 --> 28:17.822
AND THAT WOULD DO IT,
I THINK.

28:17.860 --> 28:18.895
[both chuckling]

28:18.930 --> 28:22.388
- LUCKY.
- THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

28:22.420 --> 28:23.170
I'LL BUY YOU A BEER. COME ON.
- YEAH.

28:23.210 --> 28:25.838
- CAN WE GET TWO MORE,
PLEASE?

28:25.870 --> 28:27.838
- SO WHEN DID YOU LOSE HER?

28:27.870 --> 28:28.859
- LOSE WHO?

28:28.910 --> 28:31.970
- YOUR WIFE.
MINE WAS IN '99.

28:32.020 --> 28:34.488
- I DIDN'T LOSE MY WIFE.
MY WIFE'S NOT DEAD.

28:34.540 --> 28:35.768
WHAT MADE YOU THINK THAT,
FOR CRYING OUT LOUD?

28:35.810 --> 28:37.801
- SORRY.

28:37.850 --> 28:40.535
I GUESS I JUST ASSUMED.
- ASSUMED WHAT?

28:40.580 --> 28:43.469
- THAT YOU WERE A LONELY-HEARTS
WIDOWER LIKE ME.

28:43.510 --> 28:45.296
- I'M NOT
A LONELY-HEARTS WIDO--

28:45.340 --> 28:49.856
MY WIFE HAPPENS TO BE IN ITALY
ON A TRIP WITH HER ART CLASS,

28:49.900 --> 28:52.960
AND THEY'RE SEEING MUSEUMS
AND TOUCHING STATUES.

28:53.000 --> 28:56.174
THEY'RE GOING ALL AROUND
SPENDING MY MONEY,

28:56.210 --> 28:57.791
THAT'S WHAT TH EY'RE--
I DON'T KNOW WHAT THE HELL

28:57.830 --> 28:58.933
THEY'RE DOING OVER THERE.

28:58.970 --> 29:02.246
- SOUNDS LIKE YOU'RE
A LITTLE PERTURBED ABOUT THAT.

29:02.290 --> 29:04.008
- WELL, I'M A LITTLE PERTURBED,
YEAH.

29:04.050 --> 29:07.804
I MEAN, IT'S BEEN THREE WEEKS.
I HAVEN'T HAD A GOOD MEAL,

29:07.840 --> 29:09.398
AND I DON'T HAVE
ANY CLEAN UNDERWEAR.

29:09.430 --> 29:12.297
I MEAN, COME ON. YOU KNOW?
AND THEN SHE JUST TOLD ME

29:12.330 --> 29:14.912
SHE WANTS TO STAY AN EXTRA WEEK.
I MEAN, GOD.

29:14.960 --> 29:18.191
- [laughs]
TYPICAL ARMY.

29:18.230 --> 29:21.506
CAN'T SEE THE FOREST
FOR THE TREES.

29:21.550 --> 29:24.439
- WHAT THE HELL
IS THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

29:24.480 --> 29:27.517
- MOST WOMEN OUR AGE
ARE A PAIN IN THE ASS.

29:27.550 --> 29:28.539
MANY JUST WANT TO SIT AROUND
PLAYING CARDS

29:28.590 --> 29:32.071
OR SHOWING YOU PICTURES
OF THEIR GRANDKIDS.

29:32.110 --> 29:35.489
THEY SIT THERE YAMMERING ABOUT
"MY HEARING AID THIS,"

29:35.530 --> 29:37.009
AND, "MY ARTIFICIAL HIP THAT."
IT'S ENOUGH TO DRIVE YOU CRAZY.

29:37.050 --> 29:42.329
- WELL, YOU KNOW,
CAMILLE ISN'T THAT WAY AT ALL.

29:42.360 --> 29:45.227
- THEN BE THANKFUL.

29:47.540 --> 29:50.293
I'M TELLING YOU,
IF MY WIFE WAS STILL ALIVE,

29:50.340 --> 29:53.889
AND SHE ASKED ME
TO TAKE A TRIP TO ITALY,

29:53.930 --> 29:58.264
I'D BUY TWO FIRST-CLASS TICKETS
AND BEAT HER ASS TO THE AIRPORT.

30:00.310 --> 30:03.029
BUT THAT'S JUST ME.

30:07.080 --> 30:09.548
- AND NOW FOR THE HIGHLIGHT
OF OUR EVENING.

30:09.600 --> 30:13.070
- [whispering] PUT THAT AWAY.
- IN 2003, DR. CARL FLETCHER

30:13.120 --> 30:16.396
FOUNDED GLOBAL MED WORLD SERVICE
WITH THE GOAL OF PROVIDING

30:16.430 --> 30:18.352
SUSTAINABLE HEALTHCARE
IN COUNTRIES

30:18.400 --> 30:21.392
WHERE EVEN THE MOST BASIC NEEDS
ARE NOT MET.

30:21.440 --> 30:25.194
- WAIT A MINUTE.
ARE YOU ABOUT TO GET AN AWARD?

30:25.230 --> 30:27.289
- IT'S NO BIG DEAL.
IT'S NOTHING.

30:27.340 --> 30:30.400
- IT'S A VERY BIG DEAL.
OH, MY GOD.

30:30.440 --> 30:31.998
- AND TONIGHT'S RECIPIENT

30:32.030 --> 30:36.205
OF THE HEALTHCARES VISIONARY
AWARD, DR. CARL FLETCHER.

30:36.240 --> 30:37.104
- BE RIGHT BACK.
RIGHT BACK.

30:42.910 --> 30:45.970
THANK YOU, JANE AND MELISSA.
THANKS SO MUCH.

30:46.010 --> 30:48.899
OH, THIS IS NICE.

30:48.950 --> 30:52.568
WELL, I AM TERRIBLE AT SPEECHES,
BUT I'LL JUST SAY TWO THINGS.

30:52.600 --> 30:55.012
FIRST,
IN THE NONPROFIT WORLD,

30:55.060 --> 30:58.575
THERE'S NO SUCH THING
AS AN INDIVIDUAL AWARD.

30:58.610 --> 31:01.602
GLOBAL MED
IS A TOTAL TEAM EFFORT,

31:01.650 --> 31:02.924
AND I'D LIKE TO THANK

31:02.960 --> 31:06.191
MY BRILLIANTLY TALENTED
EXECUTIVE STAFF.

31:06.240 --> 31:08.959
NOEL, THOMAS, ELAINE,
STAND UP, GUYS.

31:09.000 --> 31:11.992
[applause]

31:12.040 --> 31:15.009
THANK YOU.
THESE THREE MAKE IT HAPPEN.

31:15.040 --> 31:16.621
THEY'RE THE REASON
GLOBAL MED WORKS.

31:16.660 --> 31:20.357
SECOND, I WANT TO THANK YOU,
BECAUSE WITHOUT YOUR HELP...

31:22.050 --> 31:25.087
- [laughing] OH, MY GOD,
YOUR FRIEND NATALIE

31:25.120 --> 31:27.327
WAS SO WASTED.
- YEAH, SHE WAS

31:27.360 --> 31:30.488
IN RARE FORM TONIGHT.
SHE DEFINITELY WAS.

31:30.540 --> 31:34.397
- DO YOU THINK SHE'S JEALOUS
OR SOMETHING?

31:34.440 --> 31:37.648
- SHE'S JEALOUS OF WHAT?
- I DON'T KNOW, OF ME.

31:37.680 --> 31:39.500
SHE JUST SEEMS--
- [laughs]

31:39.550 --> 31:42.929
- WHAT?
SHE SEEMED VERY POSSESSIVE.

31:42.970 --> 31:45.063
- WE'RE FRIENDS.
I DON'T KNOW.

31:45.110 --> 31:47.658
- REALLY?
- YEAH, REALLY.

31:47.690 --> 31:48.418
- REALLY, REALLY?

31:48.450 --> 31:50.486
- YES, DOUBLE REALLY,
I SWEAR.

31:50.520 --> 31:51.726
- DOUBLE REALLY? OKAY.
[laughing]

31:51.770 --> 31:54.352
- EVERYONE REALLY LIKED YOU,
BY THE WAY.

31:54.390 --> 31:56.039
- YEAH?
- YEAH.

31:56.080 --> 31:59.629
- ALL RIGHT. OKAY.

31:59.670 --> 32:03.015
- I'M SAD YOU'RE LEAVING.

32:03.050 --> 32:06.918
- I MISSED YOU, DREW.
- YEAH.

32:08.160 --> 32:14.542
- AND I WAS THINKING
ABOUT IT TONIGHT, JUST...

32:14.580 --> 32:16.400
AND WATCHING YOU
WITH ALL YOUR FRIENDS,

32:16.450 --> 32:19.613
AND YOU'RE JUST
SUCH AN AMAZING GUY,

32:19.660 --> 32:24.245
AND I ALWAYS HAVE
SO MUCH FUN WITH YOU.

32:24.280 --> 32:31.072
I FEEL REALLY HORRIBLE ABOUT
THE WAY THINGS ENDED BETWEEN US.

32:32.570 --> 32:34.526
- YEAH, THAT WAS BAD.

32:38.710 --> 32:43.989
YOU KNOW, I--
I GET IT, THOUGH.

32:44.030 --> 32:48.057
I DO.
- I'M REALLY SORRY, DREW.

32:48.100 --> 32:50.989
YOU WERE THERE FOR ME,
AND...

32:51.030 --> 32:54.682
IT'S TAKEN ME A RIDICULOUSLY
LONG TIME TO FIGURE THAT OUT,

32:54.730 --> 33:00.453
BUT I HAVE NOW, AND I WISH
I COULD TAKE IT ALL BACK.

33:00.490 --> 33:07.419
HAVE A DO-OVER, BUT...
I CAN'T, SO...

33:07.460 --> 33:09.143
WILL YOU FORGIVE ME?

33:09.190 --> 33:15.197
- YEAH. YEAH.
I FORGIVE YOU.

33:15.230 --> 33:18.085
[Vashti Bunyan's
Train Songplaying]

33:24.140 --> 33:26.199
- TRAVELING NORTH,
TRAVELING NORTH

33:26.240 --> 33:29.232
- THANK YOU.
- YEAH, YOU'RE WELCOME.

33:29.280 --> 33:33.341
- TRAIN WHEELS BEATING,
WIND IN MY EYES

33:33.390 --> 33:38.145
DON'T EVEN KNOW WHAT
I'LL FIND WHEN I GET TO YOU

33:38.180 --> 33:42.560
CALL OUT YOUR NAME, LOVE,
DON'T BE SURPRISED

33:42.600 --> 33:46.843
IT'S SO MANY MILES
AND SO LONG SINCE I LEI-T YOU

33:46.880 --> 33:48.256
DON'T EVEN KNOW WHAT
I'LL FIND WHEN

33:48.300 --> 33:51.121
- YOU KNOW,
I PROBABLY SHOULDN'T DRIVE.

33:51.160 --> 33:55.199
- YEAH. YEAH, MAYBE
YOU COULD JUST CRASH HERE.

33:55.240 --> 33:59.165
- IT'S MANY HUNDRED MILES
AND IT WON'T

33:59.200 --> 34:02.727
BE LONG

34:02.760 --> 34:04.136
- [sighs]

34:06.110 --> 34:08.271
- WHAT THE HELL?

34:08.320 --> 34:09.867
WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON?
- I DON'T KNOW.

34:09.900 --> 34:11.140
HE'S DRUNK,
AND HE WANTED TO TALK TO ME,

34:11.180 --> 34:15.731
AND I DID NOT WANT TO TALK
TO HIM IN THAT STATE, YOU KNOW?

34:15.770 --> 34:18.705
I'M SORRY.

34:21.400 --> 34:22.742
ARE YOU OKAY?

34:22.780 --> 34:25.601
- ARE YOU HAVING AN AFFAIR
WITH ED?

34:28.270 --> 34:29.669
- NO.
- JULIA.

34:29.720 --> 34:32.336
- BABE--
- IF THERE'S ANYTHING...

34:34.270 --> 34:39.298
IF THERE IS ANYTHING GOING ON,
IF THERE'S ANYTHING AT ALL,

34:39.350 --> 34:41.511
YOU HAVE TO--
YOU HAVE TO TELL ME.

34:41.560 --> 34:42.891
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?
- JOEL,

34:42.940 --> 34:44.271
THERE'S NOTHING GOING ON.
- I NEED TO KNOW.

34:44.320 --> 34:47.596
I NEED TO KNOW.
JUST--

34:47.630 --> 34:50.497
- THERE'S NOTHING GOING ON.

34:51.880 --> 34:54.394
OKAY?

34:58.750 --> 35:02.504
- I DON'T KNOW.

35:02.540 --> 35:04.269
I DON'T KNOW
IF I CAN BELIEVE THAT.

35:04.300 --> 35:06.473
_ W--

35:06.510 --> 35:08.887
- ARE YOU SOBER?

35:08.930 --> 35:10.750
- WHAT ARE YOU--
- ARE YOU SOBER?

35:10.790 --> 35:12.849
ARE YOU--CAN YOU DRIVE?
ARE YOU SAFE?

35:12.900 --> 35:14.174
- YEAH.

35:14.210 --> 35:16.349
- TAKE THE KEYS,
AND YOU CAN DRIVE.

35:16.390 --> 35:18.381
I'M GONNA FIND A CAB,
OR SOMETHING.

35:18.420 --> 35:19.273
- JOEL, YOU DON'T--

35:33.370 --> 35:36.715
- I DON'T LIKE DANCING SO MUCH,
BUT I LIKE MUSIC.

35:36.750 --> 35:37.671
- I FEEL LIKE
YOU'RE A PRETTY GOOD DANCER.

35:37.720 --> 35:38.709
- NO!
- YEAH.

35:38.750 --> 35:40.741
- I'M NOT A GOOD DANCER.
- YES.

35:40.790 --> 35:43.475
- [sighs]
SO THANKS, THAT WAS FUN.

35:43.520 --> 35:44.544
- YEAH, GOOD.
I'M GLAD YOU HAD FUN.

35:44.590 --> 35:46.615
- IT'S NOT EVERY DAY
MY DATE GETS

35:46.660 --> 35:49.174
ONE OF THOSE CRYSTAL JOBBERS.
- TA-DA.

35:49.210 --> 35:50.620
BUT I WASN'T YOUR DATE.

35:50.660 --> 35:53.652
I WAS YOUR PLUS-ONE.
- RIGHT.

35:53.700 --> 35:55.588
- RIGHT?
- YEAH.

35:55.630 --> 35:58.190
SO...

35:58.220 --> 36:00.279
I'M NOT GONNA ASK YOU IN.

36:00.330 --> 36:02.730
- I'M NOT COMING IN,
BECAUSE SOMEBODY MADE ME PROMISE

36:02.780 --> 36:05.465
THAT TONIGHT WOULDN'T BE
ABOUT SLEEPING WITH HER,

36:05.500 --> 36:08.321
AND I'M A MAN OF MY WORD.
CARL FLETCHER.

36:08.370 --> 36:11.601
- [laughs] DR. CARL FLETCHER.
WHO KEEPS THAT TO THEMSELVES?

36:11.650 --> 36:12.537
- SO THANK YOU.

36:12.580 --> 36:14.889
- THANK YOU.

36:14.930 --> 36:17.819
- GOOD NIGHT.
- GOOD NIGHT.

36:19.000 --> 36:21.446
- JUST SO YOU KNOW, HERE'S
WHAT YOU'RE MISSING TONIGHT.

36:21.480 --> 36:22.617
- DON'T DO THAT EVER AGAIN.

36:22.660 --> 36:25.242
WAIT, DO IT ONE MORE TIME.

36:25.280 --> 36:26.895
[both laugh]

36:26.940 --> 36:28.658
[footsteps going upstairs]

36:34.880 --> 36:37.735
- MORNING.
- MORNING.

36:40.780 --> 36:42.884
YOU'RE GOING HOME TODAY,
RIGHT?

36:42.920 --> 36:45.741
- YEAH. YEAH, I AM.
- HMM.

36:45.780 --> 36:49.614
HAVE A GOOD TRIP.
- THANK YOU.

36:50.720 --> 36:53.609
FEEL BETTER.

36:57.520 --> 36:59.750
- HEY, YOU GOOD ON TIME?
- YEAH.

36:59.800 --> 37:02.030
MY FLIGHT DOESN'T LEAVE
FOR ANOTHER COUPLE HOURS.

37:02.080 --> 37:02.933
- OH.

37:07.530 --> 37:08.599
- I DON'T WANT TO GO.

37:08.640 --> 37:09.868
- YEAH.

37:09.910 --> 37:14.779
- NO, I MEAN, LIKE...
I DON'T WANT TO GO BACK.

37:14.810 --> 37:18.769
- WHAT ABOUT YOUR PARENTS?
YOU HAVE CLASS.

37:18.820 --> 37:21.948
- WELL, MY PARENTS, THEY'RE
OUT OF TOWN AS OF AN HOUR AGO,

37:21.990 --> 37:25.448
AND PEOPLE MISS CLASS
ALL THE TIME.

37:25.480 --> 37:27.926
IT'S NOT LIKE--
- YEAH, THAT'S TRUE.

37:27.960 --> 37:30.827
- DO YOU WANT ME TO SAY?

37:30.860 --> 37:32.589
- YEAH. YEAH, I DO.

37:32.620 --> 37:34.508
- [chuckles]

37:39.010 --> 37:41.899
[melancholy ballad plays]

37:55.130 --> 37:58.645
SIMPLE PLANS

37:58.690 --> 38:03.923
DON'T BE HERE

38:03.970 --> 38:10.967
OH OH OH

38:12.110 --> 38:14.829
OH OH OH

38:14.870 --> 38:15.734
- AHH.

38:40.490 --> 38:41.411
- OH! ARE YOU GONNA GET ME?
- GUYS, GUYS, WAIT.

38:41.450 --> 38:43.133
- HONEY, LOOK WHO'S HERE.
LOOK OUT, KIDS.

38:43.180 --> 38:45.523
- I'M GONNA FEED YOU.
HOLD ON.

38:45.560 --> 38:47.721
- HI, HANK.
- HEY, HOW ARE YOU?

38:47.770 --> 38:48.623
SORRY I'M BARGING IN HERE.
- I'M WELL, HOW ARE YOU?

38:48.670 --> 38:50.046
- IT'S ALL RIGHT.
- YOU'RE NOT AT ALL.

38:50.080 --> 38:51.490
- JUST WANTED TO GIVE THAT
BACK TO YOU.

38:51.530 --> 38:53.418
THANK YOU. YEAH.
- OH, YEAH. WOW.

38:53.460 --> 38:54.427
WHAT--WHAT HAPPENED HERE?
LOOKS LIKE YOU--

38:54.470 --> 38:56.665
- YEAH, I DID--I PUT
A FEW EARMARKS ON IT.

38:56.710 --> 38:58.018
I DID SOME NOTES AND, UH--
- IT'S ALL RIGHT.

38:58.050 --> 38:59.460
- MIGHT HAVE GOT SOME FOOD
ON THERE, OR SOMETHING.

38:59.500 --> 39:00.535
I READ IT A LOT.

39:00.570 --> 39:01.741
- WAS IT HELPFUL?
- YEAH.

39:01.780 --> 39:05.090
UH, IT'S--
YOU KNOW, INTERESTING.

39:05.130 --> 39:07.610
- YEAH.
- LEARNED A COUPLE THINGS.

39:07.650 --> 39:09.709
COUPLE THINGS.
HEY, ANOTHER ONE.

39:09.760 --> 39:11.136
- GREAT.
- JEEZ, YOU GUYS.

39:11.170 --> 39:12.512
YOU'RE LIKE RABBITS IN HERE.
- [laughs] NO, IT'S--

39:12.550 --> 39:13.517
- OH, NO. IT'S NOT OURS.

39:13.550 --> 39:15.108
- IT'S OUR NIECE, AIDA.

39:15.140 --> 39:17.654
- UM, IS MAX AROUND?
- YEAH.

39:17.700 --> 39:19.179
- HE'S ACTUALLY UPSTAIRS.

39:19.210 --> 39:21.553
- YEAH, COULD I TALK TO HIM?
I DON'T--YOU KNOW--

39:21.600 --> 39:23.795
IF IT ISN'T WEIRD, I JUST
WANTED TO SEE HOW HE'S DOING.

39:23.840 --> 39:24.761
- NO, I THINK THAT
WOULD BE GOOD.

39:24.810 --> 39:26.186
- YEAH.
- YEAH.

39:26.220 --> 39:27.005
- YEAH, CAN'T GUARANTEE
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN,

39:27.050 --> 39:28.802
BUT GIVE IT A KNOCK.
- ALL RIGHT.

39:28.840 --> 39:30.637
YEAH, I MEAN,
LET ME SEE WHAT HE SAYS.

39:30.670 --> 39:33.491
THAN KS.
- ALL RIGHT.

39:40.480 --> 39:43.096
- MAD MAX, HOW YOU DOING, BUDDY?
WHAT'S UP?

39:45.210 --> 39:47.542
- THIS IS WEIRD.

39:47.590 --> 39:50.753
WHY ARE YOU STANDING
IN MY BEDROOM DOORWAY?

39:50.800 --> 39:53.075
- I WAS JUST HERE.
I WAS VISITING YOUR MOM AND DAD,

39:53.110 --> 39:55.453
AND THEY SAID
YOU WERE UP HERE.

39:55.490 --> 39:59.597
JUST THOUGHT I'D COME UP,
SEE HOW YOU'RE DOING.

39:59.630 --> 40:01.143
CAN I COME IN?

40:01.190 --> 40:05.183
- IF I SAY NO,
WILL YOU GO AWAY?

40:05.230 --> 40:08.870
- NO, PROBABLY NOT.

40:08.920 --> 40:11.844
- COME IN.

40:15.860 --> 40:17.191
- SO THESE LOOK PRETTY COOL.
YOU DID THESE?

40:17.240 --> 40:18.719
YOU MAKE THESE YOURSELF?

40:18.760 --> 40:20.443
- YOU DON'T MAKE PICTURES.
YOU DRAW THEM.

40:20.480 --> 40:22.516
- WELL, THEY'RE COOL.
I USED TO DO STUFF LIKE THAT.

40:22.550 --> 40:24.654
NOT AS GOOD.

40:24.690 --> 40:28.205
HEY, I BROUGHT THE PICTURES
THAT YOU DID.

40:28.250 --> 40:30.104
THEY'RE GOOD,
JUST LIKE YOU SAID,

40:30.150 --> 40:32.072
THEY'RE REALLY GOOD.

40:32.110 --> 40:35.637
THIS ONE I LIKE.
I LIKE THE WATER FOUNTAIN.

40:35.670 --> 40:36.944
YOU KNOW, YOU GOT
A NICE LITTLE FLARE THERE.

40:36.980 --> 40:38.709
THIS ONE'S PRETTY COOL.

40:38.740 --> 40:40.492
I THINK IT'S A PIGEON,
OR SOMETHING. I DON'T KNOW.

40:40.540 --> 40:42.747
- NO, IT'S A DOVE.

40:42.780 --> 40:45.601
- OH, IS IT A DOVE?
- LET ME SEE.

40:50.620 --> 40:52.190
I'M SORRY THAT I YELLED AT YOU

40:52.240 --> 40:55.755
AND THREW THINGS
INSIDE OF YOUR STORE.

40:55.790 --> 40:57.132
I UNDERSTAND
THAT THERE'S A DIFFERENCE

40:57.170 --> 40:59.229
BETWEEN A PROMISE AND A LIE,
AND THAT IT'S NOT NICE

40:59.280 --> 41:02.249
TO ACCUSE SOMEONE OF DISHONESTY
IN A CASUAL MANNER.

41:02.280 --> 41:05.249
I RESPECT YOUR TIME
AND THE WORK THAT YOU DO.

41:05.290 --> 41:07.906
WILL YOU ACCEPT MY APOLOGY?
- [chuckles]

41:07.940 --> 41:09.999
- MY PARENTS SAID
THAT IF I APOLOGIZE,

41:10.050 --> 41:12.666
WE'LL BE FRIENDS AGAIN.

41:12.710 --> 41:14.917
- YEAH.

41:14.950 --> 41:18.249
APOLOGY ACCEPTED.

41:20.580 --> 41:22.150
- DO YOU WANT TO PLAY CHESS?

41:22.200 --> 41:25.886
I'M NOT VERY GOOD,
BUT IF I PLAY MORE, I'LL LEARN.

41:25.930 --> 41:28.922
- YEAH, I'LL PLAY CHESS.
I PLAY A LITTLE CHESS.

41:28.960 --> 41:30.848
- I LIKE TO BE BLACK, BUT
IF YOU HAVE A COLOR PREFERENCE,

41:30.900 --> 41:32.925
I CAN BE FLEXIBLE.
- NO, I'LL BE WHITE.

41:32.970 --> 41:35.063
- GOOD, THAT MAKES THINGS
A LOT EASIER.

41:35.110 --> 41:36.725
- CAN I MOVE THIS OVER?

41:36.770 --> 41:37.862
[groans]
- GO.

41:37.900 --> 41:40.596
- YOU'RE NOT GONNA GET UPSET
IF I BEAT YOU, RIGHT?

41:40.630 --> 41:42.211
- JUST MOVE YOUR PIECES.

41:42.250 --> 41:44.639
- 'CAUSE I LIKE TO PLAY TO WIN.

41:44.670 --> 41:47.878
[low chatter]

41:47.910 --> 41:54.918
- OH OH OH
